#: ../../D/demo-mode.rst:5
msgid "demo mode"
msgstr "demo mode"

#: ../../D/demo-mode.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../D/demo-mode.rst:10
msgid ""
"[Sun] The state of being :ref:`heads-down` in order to finish code in time "
"for a :ref:`demo`\\, usually due yesterday."
msgstr ""
"[Sun] \\ :ref:`demo`\\ に間に合わせてコードを仕上げるために\\ :ref:`heads-down`\\ "
"になっている状態。たいていは昨日が締め切りである。"

#: ../../D/demo-mode.rst:13
msgid ""
"A mode in which video games sit by themselves running through a portion of "
"the game, also known as attract mode. Some serious :ref:`app`\\s have a demo"
" mode they use as a screen saver, or may go through a demo mode on startup "
"(for example, the Microsoft Windows opening screen — which lets you impress "
"your neighbors without actually having to put up with :ref:`Microsloth-"
"Windows`\\)."
msgstr ""
"ビデオゲームが自分でゲームの一部分を実行して放置されている、attract mode(アトラクトモード)としても知られるモード。一部の本格的な\\ "
":ref:`app`\\ は、スクリーンセーバーとして使うdemo modeを持っていたり、起動時にdemo "
"modeを通過したりする(たとえばMicrosoft Windowsの起動画面——実際に\\ :ref:`Microsloth-Windows`\\ "
"に我慢することなく近所の人々に感心してもらえる)。"
